{"title": "The Handler", "content": "A character type in Spy Fiction, particularly in those which lean in the Government Conspiracy direction and/or those with assassins as their protagonists. The heroes don't have access to their bosses, but instead have orders relayed to them through the \"Handler\" whose jobs include looking out for the hero's physical and emotional well-being and/or killing the hero should they act out of line. In cases with the hero and Handler being of different genders, it is somewhat common for the Handler to have Unresolved Sexual Tension with the hero as they are the \"human face\" of the secret organization to which the hero belongs.\n\nIf the Handler is officially part of a government agency, the more accurate term would be \"case officer\", whereas the people s/he is handling are known as \"agents\".\n\nSee also Mission Control, Mysterious Employer. The handler's handler is The Spymaster.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheHandler", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DarkerThanBlack", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/GunslingerGirl", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/WeissKreuz", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Claymore", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/RODTheTV", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DeathNote", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MaidenRose", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FullmetalAlchemist", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/HaruhiSuzumiya", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/JojosBizarreAdventure", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Red", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheKiller", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheBourneSeries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/MacheteKills", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Nikita", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AmericanUltra", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheRecruit", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Quiller", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheCulture", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/UseOfWeapons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ThePlayerOfGames", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JohnLeCarre", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JohnLeCarre", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literatur